What is AWS Organizations?

AWS Organizations is a service to centrally manage multiple AWS accounts under one root. It provides consolidated billing, 
SCPs to enforce policies across all accounts, and OUs to group accounts by environment or department.

It is a service that helps you manage multiple AWS accounts centrally from one place.

Simple Analogy

Without AWS Organizations:
Each AWS account is separate
Different billing, different policies
You login to each account separately
→ hard to manage

With AWS Organizations:
All accounts under ONE umbrella
Single billing, central policies
Manage all from one place
→ like a company with departments

Structure

Root (Top Level)
      │
      ├── Management Account (Master)
      │         └── pays all bills
      │
      ├── OU (Organizational Unit)
      │     ├── Dev Account
      │     └── Test Account
      │
      ├── OU Production
      │     ├── Prod Account
      │     └── DR Account
      │
      └── OU Security
            ├── Log Archive Account
            └── Audit Account

| Feature              | What it does                             |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Consolidated Billing | Single bill for all accounts             |
| SCPs                 | Apply policies across all accounts       |
| OUs                  | Group accounts by department/environment |
| Account Factory      | Create new accounts automatically        |


SCP — Service Control Policy

Management Account applies SCP
          │
          ▼
    All child accounts
    automatically follow

Example SCP:
"No one can disable CloudTrail"
→ applies to Dev, Staging, Prod
→ even account root user cannot bypass
---------
Consolidated Billing Benefit

Without Organizations:
  Dev Account     → separate bill
  Prod Account    → separate bill
  Security Account → separate bill

With Organizations:
  All accounts → ONE bill
                + volume discounts
                + easy cost tracking
---------
Control Tower vs Organizations

AWS Organizations    =  Foundation (the structure)
AWS Control Tower    =  Built on top of Organizations
                        (adds guardrails, automation,
                         dashboard, account factory)

Control Tower needs Organizations to work
Organizations can work without Control Tower
